1
00:00:41,207 --> 00:00:43,668
Dad, I need to use the restroom.

2
00:01:27,003 --> 00:01:28,213
I'm

3
00:01:29,589 --> 00:01:30,882
moving to Seoul

4
00:01:31,716 --> 00:01:33,218
with Hwang Hui-tae.

5
00:01:35,345 --> 00:01:36,721
I heard.

6
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:41,559
You're smiling?

7
00:01:42,644 --> 00:01:44,312
Kim Myeong-hee.

8
00:01:44,395 --> 00:01:45,814
How can you

9
00:01:46,773 --> 00:01:48,525
smile at me right now?

10
00:01:50,193 --> 00:01:51,319
Su-ryeon.

11
00:02:02,705 --> 00:02:04,332
You must have a lot on your mind

12
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:07,252
now that you're actually leaving.

13
00:02:09,671 --> 00:02:10,755
No.

14
00:02:13,007 --> 00:02:16,886
Su-ryeon, you remind me of myself
when I was young.

15
00:02:23,685 --> 00:02:25,395
If you let fear rule your life,

16
00:02:26,271 --> 00:02:28,648
you'll be daunted by more and more things

17
00:02:29,315 --> 00:02:31,526
to the point that you can't do anything.

18
00:02:31,609 --> 00:02:35,071
And if that happens,
you'll become even more fearful.

19
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:01,848
When you get there,

20
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:05,059
don't get dragged into trouble.
Go straight home.

21
00:03:06,311 --> 00:03:07,353
Okay.

22
00:03:10,064 --> 00:03:12,775
You must've been uncomfortable
because of me.

23
00:03:12,859 --> 00:03:13,943
I'm sorry.

24
00:03:15,987 --> 00:03:17,030
No, not at all.

25
00:03:17,947 --> 00:03:19,532
Take good care of Su-ryeon.

26
00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:21,826
I will.

27
00:03:23,077 --> 00:03:25,788
Goodness. I'm not on the verge of dying
or something.

28
00:03:25,872 --> 00:03:27,624
What's with your faces?

29
00:03:28,207 --> 00:03:29,167
Su-ryeon.

30
00:03:30,084 --> 00:03:32,295
Are you sure you'll be okay?

31
00:03:34,589 --> 00:03:36,007
Yes, of course!

32
00:03:36,966 --> 00:03:39,886
Your troublemaker daughter
won't be around anymore,

33
00:03:40,595 --> 00:03:42,639
so take care of your health, Dad.

34
00:03:57,487 --> 00:03:58,488
Well…

35
00:04:00,156 --> 00:04:03,368
I don't want to make you cringe,
so let's skip the hug.

36
00:04:04,661 --> 00:04:05,912
I'll get going now.

37
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:11,751
Su-ryeon.

38
00:04:12,543 --> 00:04:15,546
Come back anytime
if things don't work out.

39
00:04:38,945 --> 00:04:40,947
SEOUL

40
00:04:59,882 --> 00:05:03,011
I can't believe he left like this.

41
00:05:04,387 --> 00:05:06,848
Hui-tae!

42
00:05:07,432 --> 00:05:09,934
He had to go back to Seoul
because he lives there.

43
00:05:10,018 --> 00:05:11,936
Did you think he'd live here forever?

44
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:15,398
Good grief. You're being ridiculous.

45
00:05:16,691 --> 00:05:19,777
Are you sure
you don't want to head out with me?

46
00:05:19,861 --> 00:05:22,947
I told you I'm not in the mood
to go anywhere!

47
00:05:24,574 --> 00:05:28,745
What do you mean? Get ready for school!
You're not even in your uniform yet!

48
00:05:28,828 --> 00:05:31,039
-No!
-Get moving!

49
00:05:33,374 --> 00:05:35,585
You probably won't cry like that
when I die!

50
00:05:40,882 --> 00:05:44,260
My goodness. She's crying
as if we lost our country again.

51
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:48,890
Myeong-hee, are you…

52
00:05:54,812 --> 00:05:57,273
Hey, Myeong-hee. What are you doing?

53
00:05:57,356 --> 00:05:59,984
Why are you washing the sheets so early?

54
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:01,194
What's up?

55
00:06:01,778 --> 00:06:05,281
I have to visit my hometown for a few days
to take care of something.

56
00:06:05,364 --> 00:06:08,659
Then leave your sheets out.
I'll wash them for you.

57
00:06:08,743 --> 00:06:11,829
What? Okay. Thanks.

58
00:06:12,955 --> 00:06:15,541
Right, can you look after Jin-a
while I'm gone…

59
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:18,544
-Sure thing. Have a safe trip.
-Okay.

60
